cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a new approach for multi-person pose estimation using a generative partition network. This involves generating partitions for multiple persons from their global joint candidates and inferring instance-specific joint configurations simultaneously. This approach involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques such as joint detection and re-organization, as well as machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) techniques such as generative models and optimization. The proposed method is evaluated on benchmarks for human pose estimation (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) applications.
